# Greeter Example — C program compiled from source
#
# This example exercises the full build pipeline:
#   1. Generate a C source file (Process recipe)
#   2. Compile it with gcc (Process recipe with dependency)
#   3. Run the compiled binary and capture output (Process recipe)
#
# Recipe hashes:
#   source:  148a1160f4afec0a893023c646f0d17050bbd49f2813ec7879c7ea47cbe9e707
#   compile: 45038849595acad2986008bfbd93ab3ba62ea3cec031fcedbf4a35ec505eb66c
#   test:    23abd18cc528b0b6f177ed88e4b26d86a2a5c384bc120b914926f9bdd593eac6
#
# Build order:
#   1. hod build examples/greeter/01-greeter-source.hod
#   2. hod build examples/greeter/02-greeter-compile.hod
#   3. hod build examples/greeter/03-greeter-test.hod
#
# Then inspect:
#   hod ls-output <output-hash> --recursive --long
